\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. L. lancifolium} Thunb., {\i Trans. Linn. Soc. London}{\b  2}: 333 (1794) ({\i L. tigrinum} Ker-Gawler). Stem 60-120(-150) cm; leaf-axils with bulbils. Leaves up to 19 × 1·7 cm, patent, linear-lanceolate, 5- to 7-veined, glabrous beneath, ciliate. Flowers 5-12, usually bracteolate; pedicels recurved. Perianth-segments c. 10 cm, recurved, bright orange, with purplish-black spots and small purplish papillae inside. Filaments reddish; anthers dark orange-red. {\i Cultivated for ornament, and naturalized in E. Austria.} [Au.] ({\i China, Japan}.)
