\pard\f0\fs28 Bulbous perennials. Bulbs usually ovoid, of free or concrescent, concentric scales, renewed each year or progressively over 2-4 years. Leaves basal. Flowers in a corymbiform or elongate raceme. Perianth-segments 6, free or scarcely connate at the base, petaloid. Stamens 6; filaments simple or 3-dentate; anthers dorsifixed, introrse. Fruit a loculicidal capsule; seeds numerous, globose to elongate-prismatic or flattened.
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28  Many characters, especially of the flowers and bulbs, can only be seen properly on live material or on material preserved in fixative; dried material is often unsuitable for determination and cannot be adequately reconstituted by boiling or other techniques.
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28  The classification adopted here relies heavily on features of the bulbs and type of germination and departs, thereby, considerably from more traditional systems.
